# Generate server certificate
python3 generate_client.py genserver

# Start OpenVPN server (Linux)
sudo openvpn --config server.conf

# Or on Windows as Administrator
openvpn --config server.ovpn


$ python generate_client.py gencfg
[✓] Server configuration generated → openvpn\server\server.ovpn

============================================================
SERVER SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
============================================================
1. Copy these files to your OpenVPN server:
   - openvpn\server\server.ovpn
   - openvpn\server\tls-crypt.key
   - openvpn\ca\ca.crt
   - openvpn\ca\crl.pem

2. On the server, install OpenVPN:
   Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt install openvpn
   CentOS/RHEL: sudo yum install openvpn

3. Start the server:
   sudo openvpn --config server.ovpn

4. For auto-start on Linux:
   sudo cp openvpn\server\openvpn-server.service /etc/systemd/system/
   sudo systemctl daemon-reload
   sudo systemctl enable openvpn-server
   sudo systemctl start openvpn-server

5. Configure firewall to allow UDP port 1194